  <span id="freeText16834535458247056229" style="display:none">This book is so intriguing - yes, I am describing a romance novel as intriguing - from the beginning to the end. Because, the plot changes so quickly that it is hard to tell what is going to happen next.<br /><br />I have really loved the character of Christian. He is not the totally dashing and perfect hero of the most historical romance novels. His imperfection makes him human.<br /><br /><a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[He has earned my respect, in the end of the novel, when Maddy comes back to him, he tells that his character is not pure like her. The male characters do not accept this in other novels. It is generally accepted that they are rogues and the girls like bad boys. <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span><br /><br />The character of Maddy is shy, but, bold when the situation demands.<br /><br /><a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[I have liked that Maddy accepts Christian's illegitimate daughter. This may not seem a big deal in this time. But, during the setting of the time of the book, it has been a crucial matter. And, Maddy vows to Christian that she will teach his daughter how to hold her head high in a society that judges people according to their birth. <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span><br /><br />I do not need to tell that this book is romantic, it is a romance novel after all. The readers who likes historical romance novels will really love it.</span>
